1. *Veče* je pala na grad. (Evening fell on the city.)
2. Dođi na *veče* kod mene. (Come over to my place for an evening gathering.)
3. *Večer* provodim sa porodicom. (I spend my evenings with my family.)
4. Ovo je *već* drugi put da mi se to dešava. (This is already the second time this has happened to me.)
5. *Veći* deo današnjeg dana sam proveo u kancelariji. (I spent most of today in the office.)
6. *Naveče* obično idem u teretanu. (I usually go to the gym in the evening.)
7. *Večeras* idemo u bioskop. (We're going to the movies tonight.)
8. *Predveče* se obično osećam umorno. (In the late afternoon, I usually feel tired.)
9. *Većina* ljudi voli leto. (Most people like summer.)
10. *Zaveče* ću pamtiti ovaj dan. (I will remember this day forever.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "veče" can be used as a noun meaning "evening," "nighttime gathering," or "evening event," as well as a part of several different adverbs and adjectives, such as "već," "veći," "naveče," "večeras," "predveče," "većina," and "zaveče," which have various meanings in English.